</p><p>MB refers to <b>megabyte</b> - a unit of information or computer sto=
rage equal to either 1,048,576 bytes (2<sup>20</sup>) or 1,000,000 bytes (1=
0<sup>6</sup>), depending on context. A megabyte has approximately 1,000 (o=
r 1,024 to be precise) kilobytes.
